# Configuration Management Guidelines

## Configuration Structure ([config.py](mdc:config.py))
- Centralize all configuration settings in a single file
- Use clear, descriptive variable names
- Group related settings together
- Provide default values where appropriate

## API Configuration
- Store IBM watsonx.ai credentials securely
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Provide fallback values for optional settings
- Document required vs optional configuration

## Model Settings
- Define LLM and embedding model IDs
- Set appropriate parameters (temperature, tokens, etc.)
- Allow for model switching and configuration
- Document model capabilities and limitations

## Query Parameters
- Set similarity search parameters
- Configure chunk sizes and processing limits
- Define response generation parameters
- Allow for parameter tuning and optimization

## Security Best Practices
- Never commit API keys to version control
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper key validation
- Provide clear instructions for setup

## Example Configuration Structure
```python
# API Configuration
WATSONX_URL = "https://us-south.ml.cloud.ibm.com"
WATSONX_PROJECT_ID = "your-project-id"
WATSONX_APIKEY = "your-api-key"

# Model Settings
LLM_MODEL_ID = "ibm/granite-3-2-8b-instruct"
EMBEDDING_MODEL_ID = "ibm/slate-125m-english-rtrvr"

# Query Settings
SIMILARITY_TOP_K = 7
TEMPERATURE = 0.0
MAX_NEW_TOKENS = 500
```

## Environment Variables
- Use environment variables for production settings
- Provide fallback to config file values
- Document required environment variables
- Implement proper validation for required settings